            <p>The history of physiotherapy dates back to ancient civilizations like China and India, with significant advancements occurring during the Renaissance and Enlightenment periods (14th 18th century). Physiotherapy became a legitimate profession through the efforts of organizations like the Society of Trained Masseuses and the impact of World War I. It has since evolved to include specialization, research, and exercise-based rehabilitation..</p>
